ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[_Xylella fastidiosa_ occurs only in the Americas. In North America the
disease is limited to areas where winters are mild, i.e. all southern
states where grapevines are grown commercially. In California, the disease
is more prevalent in wetter environments which are also areas which support
growth of vegetation upon which the leafhopper vector feeds. The disease
also occurs in Mexico and Central America. X. fastidiosa clogs the xylem
in infected plants, causing wilting and death. In California, the
bacterium causes severe diseases in grapevine, almond and alfalfa and may
be the cause of a similar disease in oleander. - Mod.DH]
